TY  - JOUR
T1  - Designing the Management System
AU  - Young, Stanley
Y1  - 1964/06/01
PY  - 1964
DA  - 1964/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255022
DO  - 10.5465/255022
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 137
EP  - 148
VL  - 7
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the process of developing a hospital management system. From a systems viewpoint, the hospital under discussion can be considered a total system composed of sub-systems, such as nursing, pharmacy, purchasing, and so forth. A discussion is presented about the development of an organizational structure and the management of responsibility for various component stages of organizational development. The component stages include raising of the organizational problem, assigning the problem to the administrative personnel or department head who is responsible for the particular sphere of operation to which the problem relates, ascertaining the nature of the problem, and searching for improved alternative solutions.
