TY  - JOUR
T1  - Organization Planning: Whose Responsibility?
AU  - Bailey, Joseph K.
Y1  - 1964/06/01
PY  - 1964
DA  - 1964/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255019
DO  - 10.5465/255019
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 95
EP  - 108
VL  - 7
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents information on a study which examined the different approaches in organizational planning of corporations in the U.S. Evidence of the variety of approaches used by the 639 companies cooperating in the preliminary phases of the study is discussed. As the analysis of preliminary responses proceeded, it was hypothesized that a large majority of the companies resolved organization planning responsibilities in one of six categories. A discussion is presented about methods used by corporations to effectively plan for the development of the organization.
